Create a repo on Git

Obtain a personal access token from git's developer settings (in case you lost your token)
Clone your repo from your linux machine to git using the below command:
        git clone https://<personal access token>@github.com/<username>/<repo>.git
        eg git clone https://ghp_kvDRqdq363kAxexBjK80Mrp...@github.com/klch-spec/alx-pre_c.git
Update your git identity using the below commands
        git config --global  user.name <username>
        git config --global user.email <mail>
Create a README.md file and update the repo using the below command
        git add <filename>
to add all files and changes, use the below command
	git add .
To confirm the changes to your repo, use the below command:
	git status (this will list all your status with descriptions and clolour codes)
Commit your changes using the below command
	git commit -m"Something descriptive for the change"
For the first time, to push to git hub, use the below command:
	git push --set-upstream https://github.com/<username>/<repo> master
	e.g. - git push --set-upstream https://github.com/klch-spec/alx-system_e... master
Finally, keep synchronizing your changes using the below command:
	git push
	provide your username
	provide your personal access token which was used to clone your repo as above

